# Response Preferences



## Documentation Files
- NEVER create documentation files (.md, .txt, docs, README, etc.) unless explicitly requested
- NEVER create example files or sample code files

## Response Style
- Keep responses SHORT and CONCISE
- Be CLEAR and CONSISTENT
- Focus on direct answers without elaboration
- Skip explanations unless specifically asked

## Code Examples
- DO NOT provide code examples unless explicitly requested
- Only show code when the user asks for it
- When editing code, just make the changes without showing examples

## Discord.js Framework
- This project uses discord.js v14.26.2 as the main library
- Essential for all Discord API interactions (events, commands, messages)
- Reference official docs: https://discord.js.org/docs/packages/discord.js/14.26.2
- Use modern discord.js patterns (slash commands, interactions, intents)

## Logging System
- Use `Logger` from `api/src/utils/Logger.ts` for all logging
- Methods: `Logger.error()`, `Logger.warning()`, `Logger.info()`, `Logger.debug()`
- Pass request object as last parameter for context
- Logs stored in PostgreSQL `system_logs` table
- View logs at: http://localhost:3003/logs or via API at `/api/logs`
- Configure via env vars: `ENABLE_LOGGING`, `LOG_LEVEL`, `LOG_RETENTION_DAYS`
